## Workforce protocol applies here

This project uses the **agentic workforce protocol** (default). The global `~/.claude/CLAUDE.md` contains the protocol details — agent roles, label conventions, board columns, slash commands, kill switches.

Project-specific config:

- **GitHub repo**: `<owner>/{{PROJECT_NAME}}`
- **Project board number**: `<NUMBER>` (one-time: set via `bash scripts/init-project.sh`)
- **Primary branch**: `main`
- **Required CI checks** (set by branch protection): `Lint`, `Typecheck`, `Test`, `Conventional commit title`, `PR size`, `Linked issue`

When a Claude Code session starts in this directory and the user asks "what should I work on" or starts work without a target, follow the global workforce protocol — query the board for unblocked `agent:*` issues and propose the highest priority.

